         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Ezra Stiles College, Yale University, Records of the Master (RU 797). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_02fe2eca8b06b255f334363d582597f7">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_0855a8610f164416800227ab61e5dfca">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of correspondence, minutes, and letters of recommendation maintained by Richard B. Sewall as master of Ezra Stiles College, Yale University.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_4e98c9298c94b194c2453c0896b348cb">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_9b2ddb52a08d8a2d4e4a7011c21c13b5">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The title "Master" for chief executive officers of residential colleges was changed to "Head of College" in April of 2016.</p>  
      </bioghist>
